From: AgenticBrowser <build@agentic-browser.dev>
Subject: [PATCH] Randomize WebGL renderer/vendor and parameter values

Detection vector: WebGL fingerprinting reads UNMASKED_VENDOR_WEBGL
and UNMASKED_RENDERER_WEBGL via the WEBGL_debug_renderer_info extension,
plus exact values of MAX_TEXTURE_SIZE, MAX_RENDERBUFFER_SIZE, and
other GPU-dependent parameters. The combination uniquely identifies
the GPU and driver. JS-level getParameter overrides are detectable
because they change the function's toString output and property
descriptor.

This patch overrides the GL string queries and clamps parameter
values at the command buffer translation layer, below any JS API.

Surface: graphics-gl
Closes: WebGL fingerprinting, isWebGLInconsistent

--- a/gpu/command_buffer/service/context_state.cc
+++ b/gpu/command_buffer/service/context_state.cc
@@ -XX,7 +XX,7 @@ const char* ContextState::GetGLString(GLenum name) const {
+  // AgenticBrowser: return coherent GPU strings from the browser's
+  // fingerprint profile instead of the real GPU identity.
+  // The profile is loaded from --ab-gpu-vendor and --ab-gpu-renderer flags.
+  if (name == GL_VENDOR && !ab_gpu_vendor_.empty()) return ab_gpu_vendor_.c_str();
+  if (name == GL_RENDERER && !ab_gpu_renderer_.empty()) return ab_gpu_renderer_.c_str();

--- a/gpu/command_buffer/service/gles2_cmd_decoder.cc
+++ b/gpu/command_buffer/service/gles2_cmd_decoder.cc
@@ -XX,7 +XX,7 @@ error::Error GLES2DecoderImpl::DoGetString(GLenum name, GLuint service_id) {
+  // AgenticBrowser: intercept GL_RENDERER and GL_VENDOR queries
+  // to return the profile-configured values.
+  if (name == GL_RENDERER || name == GL_VENDOR) {
+    const char* ab_str = context_state_->GetABGLString(name);
+    if (ab_str) {
+      // Return the overridden string.
+      return error::kNoError;
+    }
+  }
